<h3>First steps</h3>
<p>At the beginning, one thing matters most: resources. The timber camp produces wood, the clay pit produces clay and the iron mine produces iron. The more you upgrade these buildings, the higher your production. During your first days, focusing on resource production is highly recommended.</p>
<p>Besides production, you should protect your resources from raiders. Enemy attacks can steal what you worked for. The hiding place helps here: the higher its level, the more resources can be hidden from enemy troops. This is especially important if strong players are nearby. You should also upgrade your wall; even a few levels in early game can inflict meaningful losses on attackers.</p>
<p>Once basic production is set up, you can recruit troops and trade. With a Barracks (requires Headquarters level 3), you can train spearmen. While they are not ideal attackers, they let you raid weak players for resources.</p>
<p>If you prefer trading, build a Market (requires Headquarters level 3 and Warehouse level 2). There you can see neighboring villages' offers and exchange excess resources efficiently. You can also post your own offers. Keep in mind that Market level 1 gives you only one merchant, so do not overextend with too many offers.</p>
<p>You should also try to join a tribe. Together you can defend better and trade more effectively. You may also meet some helpful allies.</p>
